               <p>187, 188. 
               
                  <persName id="t17500228-10-defend80" type="defendantName">
                     Abraham 
                     Cribb 
                  <interp inst="t17500228-10-defend80" type="surname" value="Cribb"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-defend80" type="given" value="Abraham"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-defend80" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17500228-10-off40" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-off40" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-off40" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one peruke, val. 20 s.
            </rs> 
                  <rs id="t17500228-10-cd41" type="crimeDate">Nov. 18</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17500228-10-off40 t17500228-10-cd41"></join>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17500228-10-off42 t17500228-10-cd41"></join>, and 
               
                  <persName id="t17500228-10-defend82" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Beaumont 
                  <interp inst="t17500228-10-defend82" type="surname" value="Beaumont"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-defend82" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-defend82" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
            , for <rs id="t17500228-10-off42" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-off42" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-off42" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp>
               receiving the same, knowing it to be stolen
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>The only Evidence was 
               <persName id="t17500228-10-person83">
                  Charles 
                  Speckman 
               <interp inst="t17500228-10-person83" type="surname" value="Speckman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-person83" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-person83" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , an accomplice, of about fifteen years of age. Who depos'd, he himself had followed the business of thieving about two years; but not being back'd by evidence of credit, the prisoners were <rs id="t17500228-10-verdict43" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17500228-10-verdict43" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
